# Iteration 08 — Administrator can manage payment schedule calendar (Terminarz opłat)

## Goal
We want to have functionality, where user in role Administrator can configure and manage payment schedule calendar (Terminarz opłat) with detailed schedule entries per payment

## Requirements
- We will introduce a new view "Terminarz opłat"
- View is available only for users in role Administrator
- On the view a table of payments is displayed with the following columns: "Typ opłaty", "Nazwa terminarza", "Numer umowy", "Data od", "Data do"
- After selecting a row in the table, an additional table with schedule entries (PKU 12) is displayed
- Currently selected row should be visually highlighted
- After unselecting the row, the schedule entries table is hidden
- The schedule entries table contains the following columns:
  - "Pozycja terminarza" — sequential values based on PKU 12
  - "Dzień" — editable field with selection of day in range from 1 to 31
  - "Godzina" — editable field with 24-hour format selection
  - "Typ" — dropdown field with values based on PKU 13
- User can edit "Dzień", "Godzina" and "Typ" fields
- User can save changes in schedule entries
- User in role Kontrahent cannot see this view

## Acceptance criteria
- user in role Administrator after logging in can access "Terminarz opłat" view
- user in role Administrator can see table of payments with defined columns
- user in role Administrator can select and unselect a row in the table
- user in role Administrator sees highlighted selected row
- user in role Administrator sees schedule entries table after selecting a row
- user in role Administrator can edit "Dzień", "Godzina" and "Typ" fields
- user in role Administrator can save changes in schedule entries